  "prompt": "Can I apply for internet banking in Andhra bank without visiting the branch?",
  "response": "As of 2020, Andhra Bank merged with Union Bank of India. For the most up-to-date and accurate information about applying for internet banking, I recommend:\n\n1. Visit the Union Bank of India official website\n\n2. Check if online registration for internet banking is available:\n- You may be able to apply online through their internet banking portal\n- Some banks allow registration through net banking/mobile banking\n\n3. Alternative methods:\n- Call the bank's customer care number\n- Send an email to their customer support\n- Download the Union Bank mobile app and check registration process\n\n4. General requirements typically include:\n- Having an active bank account\n- Valid account credentials\n- Registered mobile number\n- PAN/Aadhaar details\n\n5. If online registration is not fully available, you might need to:\n- Visit the nearest branch\n- Fill out an internet banking registration form\n- Submit necessary documents\n\nFor the most precise and current information, I recommend:\n- Checking the Union Bank of India website\n- Calling their customer support at 1800 425 1515\n- Visiting a local branch\n\nDisclaimer: Banking processes can change, so direct communication with the bank is always recommended.",
